---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
const lang = 'en';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang={lang}>
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Agro2Code Blog</h1>
			<p>
				The Agro2Code Blog is where the portfolio topics are expanded into complete articles,
				technical notes, experiments, and practical discussions about digital agriculture,
				computing, and product development.
			</p>
			<p>
				The project is intentionally simple in delivery and reliable in operation: Markdown or
				MDX authoring, stable public URLs, static deployment on GitHub Pages, and an
				Obsidian-first editorial workflow.
			</p>
			<p>Current principles:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Publish in PT-BR first, with EN support kept available</li>
				<li>Preserve canonical URLs for predictable portfolio integration</li>
				<li>Validate content contracts before publication</li>
				<li>Evolve the product through TDD and small, reversible changes</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Use the blog navigation to browse published posts. Editorial and architecture decisions
				remain documented in the repository to keep implementation continuity over time.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
